3 things 2022 taught me <3

it’s okay to chose yourself. it’s your happiness on the line. there are inevitable inconveniences 
in this life but you should continue to chose YOU. 

social media is SO fake. it’s easy to look at someone profile and see all of these fun things they’re doing, and to see how many friends they have, and how they seemingly have the “perfect” life. but it’s important to remember that content days are a thing. 9 times out of 10 your favorite creators are shooting 12 different photos in the span of one day. and that includes me, and it comes with the job. celebrations will be caught on camera as this big wonderful surprise and a great time, but it might not be as glorious in person as it looks online. i’m speaking from experience. someone’s life can be painted out to be the “dream life” stress free, work free, and overall happy. but that’s what is chosen to be put online, and it doesn’t make it real. but it’s also important to remember that there is nothing wrong with only putting your best moments online. what someone chooses to share on the internet is ultimately up to them. 

last but not least. take the leap of faith. it’s your life to live. make your youtube videos, post your grwm’s, post your outfits. travel the world, find a job that you actually enjoy. you never know unless you try!

MY 2022 RECAP 🌊👙🥥💖🌆💌
